By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu took his campaign train to Jigawa State on Saturday where he promised to give the people of the state good lives if elected in the February 25, 2023 poll. “If you vote for me, you vote for progress, you vote for development, you vote for agricultural business, you vote for constant electricity, you vote for good life, good education. “You will get good healthcare, you will get prosperity,” he told supporters at a rally in the North-West state on Saturday. Tinubu, a former governor of Lagos State, was at the rally alongside his strong allies in the north including governors of Jigawa, Kano, Zamfara, Plateau, Borno,